    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"267205\">Nicolò Cavalleri</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/Smooth.20varieties.20are.20smooth.20manifolds/near/263195884\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span> How about the regular value theorem? I guess that could be a first step for the original project anyways</p>\n<p>But without the submanifold part, just to prove that the preimage of a regular value is a manifold</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That seems reasonable to me, but I'd check with <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110050\">@Sebastien Gouezel</span> and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110031\">@Patrick Massot</span> too.</p>",
